{
  "stem": "24268.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "She always used to send me with things.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was anonymously, so would not-- no one should know, or or that somebody know about it-- always quiet, discrete, very discrete.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Never talked about it.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Matter of fact, the same thing happened to my grandmother.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And during-- can I say how-- no.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Maybe during the war you want to tell that, that after she passed away, that was-- and she got a heart attack when a German soldier went-- jumped into the window.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And my grandma had a coffee.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 16,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And she  got a heart attack from fear.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that time-- that was in the beginning of the war.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And mom-- they told-- when they went-- came back from funeral, that there were a lot-- well, the people come and cried.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Sara, ?] who is going to take care of us?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They have always been very generous and caring, the whole family.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And, as matter of fact, they also-- when my grandfather passed away, blessed memory.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So she devoted her chandelier that looked very colorful.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I don't remember-- like in a-- like in a very vivid-- I mean, actually, like in a dream, because it's-- I'd just been very young then.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But I recall, like the colors, like have you seen those Tiffany's lights, lamps?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The colors were beautiful.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And my husband, when he went to visit after the war, with his wife and the youngest son, which he wanted to go back and see his-- where we came from.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 17,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "So this chandelier-- amazing, surprisingly-- was still hanging in the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, before the war, like I said, we-- business and my-- and everything was very successful, and a happy home.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
